        - description: Release notes in HTML format
        - pubDate: Publication date in RFC 822 format
        - enclosure: Download link with signature

        To add a new release:
        1. Build and archive your app in Xcode
        2. Export as .app
        3. Compress to .zip: ditto -c -k --sequesterRsrc --keepParent FinderHover.app FinderHover.zip
        4. Sign the .zip: /opt/homebrew/Caskroom/sparkle/2.8.0/bin/sign_update FinderHover.zip
        5. Get file size: ls -l FinderHover.zip
        6. Upload .zip to GitHub release
        7. Copy the template below and fill in the details
        -->

        <!-- Example Release (v1.1.5) - Update this with actual release -->
        <item>
            <title>Version 1.1.5</title>
            <link>https://github.com/KoukeNeko/FinderHover/releases/tag/v1.1.5</link>
            <sparkle:version>7</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.1.5</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <h2>What's New in 1.1.5</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Automatic Updates:</strong> Integrated Sparkle framework for seamless automatic updates</li>
                    <li><strong>In-App Update Installation:</strong> Updates now download and install without opening browser</li>
                    <li><strong>Secure Updates:</strong> All updates are cryptographically signed with EdDSA for security</li>
                    <li><strong>Update Preferences:</strong> Control automatic update checking in Settings</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Bug Fixes & Improvements</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Improved update notification system</li>
                    <li>Enhanced security with code signing verification</li>
                </ul>
            ]]></description>
            <pubDate>Mon, 04 Nov 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
            <enclosure
                url="https://github.com/KoukeNeko/FinderHover/releases/download/v1.1.5/FinderHover.zip"
                sparkle:version="7"
                sparkle:shortVersionString="1.1.5"
                length="REPLACE_WITH_FILE_SIZE"
                type="application/octet-stream"
                sparkle:edSignature="REPLACE_WITH_SIGNATURE" />
        </item>

